window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>As a token of appreciation for sharing your dream, Audible and DC invite you to enjoy this exclusive listen of <i>The Sound of Her Wings</i>, one of the most celebrated episodes in <i>The Sandman</i> saga. This episode is a self-contained story following Lord Morpheus (James McAvoy), King of Dreams, throughout a day with his sister, Death (Kat Dennings). Before the episode begins, you’ll get a brief overview of the story so far, told by Neil Gaiman himself.&nbsp;</p> <p>This first installment of the audio series The Sandman adapts volumes 1-3 of the graphic novel series (<i>Preludes &amp; Nocturnes</i>, <i>The Doll’s House</i>, and <i>Dream Country</i>), available exclusively on Audible July 15.</p>"; 
